The reduction in trigger reach and grip circumference increases concealability and enhances shooting ergonomics. Unlike some subcompact semiautomatic pistols that use a difficult to shoot "two-finger grip" frame, the USP Compact uses a narrow, full-hand grip frame with a choice of interchangeable extended or flush-fitting magazine floorplates. Like their large frame predecessors, USP Compacts are designed with the demanding needs of the law enforcement and military shooters in mind. Using a modified linkless Browning-type action, the USP Compact is built to take the punishment of high-energy +P loads. To reduce the length of the slide and barrel on the USP Compact, the mechanical recoil reduction system found on large frame USPs has been replaced by a specially designed flat compression spring contained in the captive recoil spring assembly by a polymer absorber bushing. title: For Trade:  Sears and Roebuck Model 2T For Trade
postcontent: Up for trade is a pretty sweet little 22T Sears and Roebuck. Based off of the venerable Winchester Model 141, it's lineage is apparent in it's utilitarian purposes. Perfect for a sunny day at the range in beautiful Florida, plinking with friends and family. Even better to teach your wonderful son (or daughter) how to harvest their first squirrel of the season. They sure don't make em like they used to. Deep bluing (roughly 80%+) still has that old world luster with a nice coat of oil. Just look at the grain on that stock! Slight dings and dents, as to be expected on a gal of her age, but you won't feel guilty taking her inna woods to put a stop to those pesky critters that dig up your cabbage garden. Crisp single action trigger makes the gun safe, yet accurate. Mechanically functioning as designed. The gun was inherited from my grandpa when he passed, God rest his soul, and it's just too emotional for me to keep it in my collection, so I'm looking to trade for something to call my own.    I apologize for labeling it as a Winchester, there wasn't an option for Sears nor Roebuck.

title: For Sale:  Winchester Repeating Arms Co. Model 1907 Semi-Auto Rifle, Last Year Production - 1958
postcontent: he Winchester Model 1907 is a blowback-operated, semi-automatic rifle produced by the Winchester Repeating Arms Company beginning in 1906 and ending in 1958. It was fed from a 5 round capacity, detachable box magazine located immediately forward of the trigger guard. The only cartridge offered by Winchester as a factory chambering in the Model 1907 was the .351 SL, designed specifically for this rifle. This rifle retains about 98% of its metal finish. The barrel shows marks through the finish on both sides of the front sight with a few more scattered along the barrel from the muzzle to the forend. There is thinning on the edges of the operating sleeve tip and the receiver. There are a few light marks on the top of the receiver, with scratches through its finish on its back edge. There are a very few very light marks on the sides of the receiver with a tiny compression mark on the upper rear edge of the ejection port. The checkering on the right side of the safety shows light wear and thinning. The markings are clear. Overall, this rifle rates in about Excellent condition.
